# Unit 1 - Task 04

## Aim
Create and use a Docker volume to share data between the host system and a container.

## Step 1: Create Directory on Host

mkdir docker-volume-demo  
cd docker-volume-demo

## Step 2: Create File

echo "Hello from Host System" > data.txt

## Step 3: Run Ubuntu Container with Volume

docker run -it --name volume-container -v $(pwd):/shared ubuntu bash

## Step 4: Access Mounted Directory

cd /shared  
ls

## Step 5: Modify File

echo "Modified inside container" >> data.txt

## Step 6: Exit Container

exit

## Verification

cat data.txt


